The paper proposes a game-theoretic approach to optimize social welfare in itinerary recommendation, which involves data-driven methods and simulations. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) for the data-driven approach, Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) for the social welfare optimization, Game Theory (cs.GT) for the game-theoretic approach, Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) for the optimization problem, and Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) for the real-world application.
